The paper deals with two problems in high-dimensional robust statistics, namely robust mean estimation and outlier detection. These are problems that are commonly studied in the machine learning and data science communities, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces a new outlier scoring method based on quantum entropy regularization, which involves concepts from information theory and quantum mechanics. This suggests that the paper may also be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper's focus on algorithms and computational complexity suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper's use of machine learning techniques and evaluation on synthetic and real data suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
